org.nineml.coffeegrinder.util

Class DefaultTreeWalker

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.nineml.coffeegrinder.util.DefaultTreeWalker
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TreeWalker

    public class DefaultTreeWalker
extends java.lang.Object
implements TreeWalker
    The default tree walker.

    The default tree walker will return every tree in the forest. It does (roughly) a pre-order traversal of the forest and returns each tree that it finds.

        public void walk()
        Description copied from interface: TreeWalker
        Walk the graph, producing the current tree.

        The walker will make calls into the TreeBuilder to construct the tree.

        If walk is called more than once, it should return the same tree each time. To advance to the next tree, call TreeWalker.next().
